<BaseLayout
  title="About Us | Section 8 Calculator"
  description="Learn about the team behind Section 8 Calculator — a free tool helping millions of renters understand Housing Choice Voucher eligibility and estimates."
>
  <article class="container prose" style="padding: 2.5rem 0 4rem; max-width: 42rem;">
    <h1>About Section 8 Calculator</h1>

    <p>
      Section 8 Calculator is a <strong>free, independent resource</strong> built to help
      low-income renters, housing counselors, and advocates understand the Housing Choice
      Voucher (Section 8) program. We index <strong>31,900+ cities and census places</strong>
      across all 50 states, Washington D.C., and Puerto Rico — each with local data, guides,
      and a ZIP-based calculator.
    </p>

    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>
      Navigating Section 8 is confusing. Income limits change every year, payment standards
      vary by ZIP code, and waiting lists open and close without warning. We believe everyone
      deserves clear, accurate information about rental assistance — without jargon, paywalls,
      or hidden agendas.
    </p>

    <h2>What We Offer</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/calculator/">Section 8 Calculator</a></strong> — Enter your ZIP code, household size, and income to see estimated eligibility and voucher amounts based on HUD data.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/section-8/">City Directory</a></strong> — Browse Section 8 information for every U.S. city and census place.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/guides/">Housing Guides</a></strong> — Plain-English guides on how Section 8 works, how to apply, income limits, and more.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/blog/">Blog</a></strong> — In-depth articles on waiting lists, city-specific voucher programs, and affordable housing news.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Sources</h2>
    <p>
      Our estimates are based on publicly available data from <strong>HUD (U.S. Department of
      Housing and Urban Development)</strong>, including Fair Market Rents, income limits, and
      Small Area Fair Market Rents. We update our data when HUD publishes new figures each year.
    </p>

    <h2>Important Note</h2>
    <p>
      Section 8 Calculator is <strong>not affiliated with HUD, any Public Housing Authority (PHA),
      or any government agency</strong>. Our tool provides educational estimates only. For official
      eligibility determinations, always contact your <a href="https://www.hud.gov/program_offices/public_indian_housing/pha/contacts">local PHA</a>.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/contact/">Contact us</a> · <a href="/disclaimer/">Disclaimer</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
